---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import { getEntry } from "astro:content";

const siteMeta = await getEntry("site", "meta");
---
<SiteLayout
  title="Huitzo: The Operating System for Intelligence | Ernesto Sola-Thomas"
  description="Huitzo is a self-hosted AI runtime that lets regulated enterprises run AI applications (Intelligence Packs) inside their own infrastructure, so sensitive data never leaves."
  siteMeta={siteMeta}
  locale="en"
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden pb-16 pt-32">
    <div aria-hidden="true" class="absolute inset-0 bg-[var(--gradient-hero)] opacity-50"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 h-32 bg-gradient-to-t from-[color:var(--surface-base)]"></div>
    <div class="container relative">
      <span class="badge">Venture</span>
      <h1 class="mt-6 font-display text-5xl font-semibold leading-tight text-primary md:text-6xl">
        Huitzo
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-xl text-secondary">
        The operating system for intelligence. AI infrastructure you actually own.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl space-y-12">
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-primary">What Huitzo Is</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Huitzo is a self-hosted AI runtime for regulated enterprises. It runs AI applications, called Intelligence Packs, inside your existing infrastructure, so sensitive data never leaves your environment. The runtime is model-agnostic: swap providers without rewriting code. Deploy it as Huitzo Cloud, self-hosted, private cloud, or hybrid.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-primary">The Problem</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          The industries with the most to gain from AI (insurance, healthcare, financial services, government, legal) are the least able to adopt it, because their data cannot leave their perimeter. Custom in-house builds take 12–18 months and a specialized team. The result is a standoff between data control and AI capability.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-primary">Why Now</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Foundation models are commoditizing; the control plane is not. What regulated organizations need is a runtime that brings models to their data, with execution logging for audit trails, isolation scoped to teams, and license-based deployment that never phones home. The window is open for infrastructure that delivers control without sacrificing capability.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-primary">Why Me</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          I verify AI acceleration silicon at Microsoft, so I understand the hardware these models run on. I have shipped production infrastructure across cloud, embedded, and research contexts. My background spans the full stack from transistors to APIs, which lets me build systems that are efficient and trustworthy at every layer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-primary">Current Stage</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          Huitzo is in active development, validating product-market fit with teams in regulated industries. I'm looking for early design partners who want AI working inside their own perimeter. This is independent work, not affiliated with Microsoft.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-primary">Vision</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          A world where any organization, regardless of regulatory constraints, can run intelligent systems it fully owns: auditable, isolated, and accountable. Not AGI hype. Practical, reliable, business-grade intelligence on your own terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 rounded-lg border border-soft bg-overlay p-8 text-center">
        <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-primary">Interested in Huitzo?</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
          Whether you're a potential design partner, investor, or just curious, I'd love to hear from you.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
          <a href="https://huitzo.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="button-primary" data-goatcounter-click="huitzo-page-visit-site">
            Visit huitzo.com
          </a>
          <a href={`mailto:${siteMeta.data.contact.email}?subject=${encodeURIComponent('Huitzo: Let\'s discuss')}`} class="button-ghost" data-goatcounter-click="huitzo-page-contact">
            Start a conversation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
